parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of a crash or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the power steering suddenly fails while driving
the steering wheel jerks or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of suspension components, such as control arms, bushings, and shock absorbers, can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
Misaligned rear suspension can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
Leaky shock absorbers can cause reduced vehicle stability, uneven tire wear, and increased risk of accidents.
Failure of front suspension bushings can cause reduced vehicle stability, uneven tire wear, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Squeaky noise from the front of the car

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire sidewall cracks and delamination can lead to sudden tire failure, loss of control, and accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Sidewall cracks ranging from one to five inches

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire wear can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distances, and accidents, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: Inside edges of rear tires wear to threads before outside edge is barely worn

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wheel damage from road debris can lead to loss of control, accidents, and wheel failure, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: often due to running over road debris such as black top.
